I"~<h4 id="what-is-a-package">What is a package?</h4>
<p>You can think of a package in latex as a library in programming language, which
provides additional functionality.</p>

<ul>
  <li>A package in latex corresponds to a file with sty extension.</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="difference-between-sty-file-and-cls-file">difference between sty file and cls file</h4>
<ol>
  <li>loading a class file via \documentclass is mandatory.
    <ul>
      <li>In the ideal case, a class file will complete define the structure of the
document, the familir article is good example: which provides commands for
typesetting, such as \section, \tableofcontents.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>package are used to provide generic functionality to any document.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="reference">Reference</h4>
<ol>
  <li><a href="http://dw.tug.org/pracjourn/2005-3/asknelly/nelly-sty-&amp;-cls.pdf">sty and cls</a></li>
</ol>
